ce:section.ce:para:
Under the optimal conditions, the working curves of SERS, RRS and Abs systems were drawn according to the experimental method. For the SERS system, the linear equation of the Apt-CDBFe-C2H2O2-HAuCl4-Pb2+ system is ΔI
                        1617cm-1 = 814726C + 953.5. For the RRS system, the linear of the same system is 1ΔI370nm = 131888C-154.8. The slope of the SERS working curve is large and the system was sensitive. It can be utilized for SERS detection of 1.3–16 pmol/L Pb2+. For the CDN system, the linear range (LR) is 1.3–16 pmol/L Pb2+, the regression equation is ΔI370nm = 76269C + 63.5, and the slope is smaller than that of CDBFe. For the Apt-CDBFe-C2H2O2-HAuCl4-Pb2+ photometric system, the linear equation is ΔA550nm = 15.6C-0.0123, the detection range is 3–16 pmol/L. The slope is small, and the photometric method is not as sensitive as the SERS and RRS methods. The novel Apt assay platform based-CDBFe catalytic amplification can be also utilized for SERS/RRS determination of trace harmful elements such as Hg2+ and As3+ respectively (Table 1
                        ). Compared with the methods that have been reported to determine lead (Table S2), this method is a very sensitive method with low instrument cost.
